@startuml consumer_sequence
title Consumer M2M Flow - Plegma Data Consumer accesses Provider's data via delegation
hide footbox

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor          #555555
    ActorBorderColor    #555555
    LifeLineBorderColor #999999
    LifeLineBackgroundColor #EEEEEE
    ParticipantBorderColor #555555
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #B3D9FF
    NoteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
    NoteBorderColor     #999999
}

actor "Consumer Application\n(EU.EORI.NLPLEGMACONSUMER)" as Consumer
participant "Keyrock IdM + AR\n(fiware-keyrock:3007)" as Keyrock
participant "iSHARE Satellite\n(ishare-satellite:8080)" as Satellite
participant "Kong API Gateway\n(kong-standalone:8000)" as Kong
participant "Orion-LD\n(fiware-orion-ld:1026)" as Orion

== Step 1: Consumer creates self-signed iSHARE JWT ==

Consumer -> Consumer : gen_consumer_token.py:\nbuild JWT with\n- iss=EU.EORI.NLPLEGMACONSUMER\n- sub=EU.EORI.NLPLEGMACONSUMER\n- aud=EU.EORI.NLPLEGMA\n- x5c=[consumer.pem, ca.pem]\nsign with consumer.key (RS256)

== Step 2: Consumer requests access token from Keyrock ==

Consumer -> Keyrock : POST /oauth2/token\ngrant_type=client_credentials\nclient_assertion_type=jwt-bearer\nclient_assertion=<iSHARE JWT>\nclient_id=EU.EORI.NLPLEGMACONSUMER

activate Keyrock

== Step 3: Keyrock validates the participant via Satellite ==

Keyrock -> Keyrock : Validate JWT signature\n& certificate chain

Keyrock -> Satellite : POST /token\n(Keyrock authenticates as EU.EORI.NLPLEGMA)
activate Satellite
Satellite --> Keyrock : access_token
deactivate Satellite

Keyrock -> Satellite : GET /parties?eori=EU.EORI.NLPLEGMACONSUMER&\ncertificate_subject_name=...&active_only=true\nAuthorization: Bearer <access_token>
activate Satellite
Satellite -> Satellite : Check parties registry:\nConsumer found,\nstatus=Active,\nfingerprint matches
Satellite --> Keyrock : parties_token\n(signed JWT with party info)
deactivate Satellite

Keyrock -> Keyrock : Verify parties_token signature\nResult: Consumer is valid participant [OK]

== Step 4: Keyrock looks up delegation policy ==

Keyrock -> Keyrock : Query DB for delegation policy:\naccess_subject = consumer's UUID\npolicy_issuer = EU.EORI.NLPLEGMA\nFOUND: Permit GET on HouseholdMeasurement

Keyrock -> Keyrock : build_access_token():\n- iss=EU.EORI.NLPLEGMA\n- sub=<consumer_uuid>\n- aud=EU.EORI.NLPLEGMACONSUMER\n- delegationEvidence={...Permit...}\nsign with provider key

Keyrock --> Consumer : 200 OK\n{access_token: <JWT with delegationEvidence>}
deactivate Keyrock

== Step 5: Consumer sends request to Kong ==

Consumer -> Kong : GET /ngsi-ld/v1/entities?type=HouseholdMeasurement\nAuthorization: Bearer <access_token>

activate Kong

== Step 6: Kong validates the access token ==

Kong -> Kong : Parse JWT, extract x5c chain

Kong -> Satellite : GET /token + GET /trusted_list
activate Satellite
Satellite --> Kong : trusted CA list
deactivate Satellite

Kong -> Kong : Verify JWT signature: VALID [OK]

== Step 7: Kong evaluates the delegation policy ==

Kong -> Kong : Token contains delegationEvidence:\n- policyIssuer=EU.EORI.NLPLEGMA\n- target.accessSubject=<consumer_uuid>\n- policies: [HouseholdMeasurement, GET, Permit]

Kong -> Kong : Match request against policy:\nGET /ngsi-ld/v1/entities?type=HouseholdMeasurement\n-> matches policy -> PERMIT [OK]

== Step 8: Kong forwards request to Orion-LD ==

Kong -> Orion : GET /ngsi-ld/v1/entities?type=HouseholdMeasurement
activate Orion
Orion --> Kong : 200 OK\n[HouseholdMeasurement entities]
deactivate Orion

Kong --> Consumer : 200 OK\n[HouseholdMeasurement entities]
deactivate Kong

@enduml
